---
title: Pan-Seared Duck Breasts with Duck-Fried Potatoes, Asparagus, and Grape Tomatoes
description: Duck is surprisingly simple to cook, and it always rewards with luscious, rich flavor—making it perfect for a special dinner. Here, you’ll be using the meat two ways: first, breasts are seared in the pan until the skin is rendered and crisp, and then the potatoes are tossed in the drippings to give them a marvelous, lingering flavor.
